@startuml numeric_hierarchy
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam classBackgroundColor #D6EAF8
skinparam classBorderColor #2E86C1

title Hierarchia typów numerycznych w Pythonie

class numbers.Number <<abstract>>
class numbers.Complex <<abstract>>
class numbers.Real <<abstract>>
class numbers.Rational <<abstract>>
class numbers.Integral <<abstract>>

class complex
class float
class fractions.Fraction
class int
class bool

numbers.Number <|-- numbers.Complex
numbers.Complex <|-- numbers.Real
numbers.Real <|-- numbers.Rational
numbers.Rational <|-- numbers.Integral

numbers.Complex <|.. complex
numbers.Real <|.. float
numbers.Rational <|.. fractions.Fraction
numbers.Integral <|.. int
int <|-- bool

note right of bool
  True == 1
  False == 0
end note

note right of float
  IEEE 754 double
  64-bit precision
end note

note right of int
  Nieograniczona precyzja
  (bignum)
end note

@enduml

